body.text:
John,

Thank you for your advice. We opened the bottles anyway and they were very, very, very, very, very fizzy. And bursty. There was a burst of fizziness eagerly escaping from the confines of the bottle, like a genie.

The beer itself was sour, not in a bad way. Kind of like a lambic. It was good. We may have been lucky this time.

Cheers,

Fronx speaking on behalf of Fronx & Tiffany
